<% content_for :title, "Stablemate — super simple job monitoring for Rails" %>
<%#
  Marketing landing page — the approved "Omakase" design direction (warm oat
  ground, Rails-red accent, Zilla Slab / Newsreader / IBM Plex Mono). All styling
  lives in app/assets/stylesheets/landing.css, scoped under `.lp` (the layout
  wraps the yield) so the authenticated app's Tailwind tokens are untouched.

  Deviations from the design mockup (all deliberate):
    * No pricing/tier/upgrade UI (locked: one Free plan) — the mockup's "Pricing"
      footer link is dropped and hosted-allowance copy flows through
      free_plan_monitors_phrase so it reads for both the capped and uncapped plan.
    * Brand uses the typographic wordmark "Stablemate." (Zilla Slab, red period)
      per the mockup, not shared/logo (that glyph stays for the authenticated app).
    * The 90-day ledger bars are rendered SERVER-SIDE via an ERB loop over
      ping_retention_days — no inline <script>; no client JS for a static viz.
    * Every "90 days" reference goes through ping_retention_days so marketing can't
      drift from the product's actual retention.
%>
<% docs_url = "https://github.com/chrisjgilbert/stablemate/blob/main/docs/integrating.md" %>
<% repo_url = "https://github.com/chrisjgilbert/stablemate" %>

