  <div class="wrap hero__grid">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">Open source · made for Rails</p>
      <h1 class="flow"><span class="nb">Super <span class="hl">simple</span></span> job monitoring for <span class="uword">Rails<svg class="scribble" viewBox="0 0 200 16" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 9 C 46 3, 92 14, 138 7 S 190 5, 196 10"/></svg></span>.</h1>
      <p class="deck">
        <span class="deck-a">Add a gem. Point it at the schedule you already keep.</span>
        <span class="deck-b">The moment a job stops running, you hear about it — <em>long before your users do.</em></span>
      </p>
      <div class="hero__cta">
        <%= link_to sign_up_path, class: "btn btn--primary" do %>Start monitoring — free <span class="arw">→</span><% end %>
        <a href="#how" class="btn btn--ghost">Show me how</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero__meta"><b>Free &amp; open source.</b> Self-host it with no limits, or let us host it — <%= free_plan_monitors_phrase %>, free.</p>
    </div>

    <figure class="figure">
      <div class="stamp"><span class="b">FREE</span><span class="s">to self-host</span></div>
      <div class="specimen">
        <div class="specimen__bar">You already wrote this <span class="fn">config/recurring.yml</span></div>
<pre class="code"><span class="c"># every job class here becomes a monitor.</span>
<span class="c"># no new code. no clicking around.</span>
<span class="k">stripe_reconcile</span>:
  <span class="k">class</span>: <span class="v">Billing::ReconcileJob</span>
  <span class="k">schedule</span>: <span class="v">every day at 3am</span>
<span class="k">daily_digest</span>:
  <span class="k">class</span>: <span class="v">DailyDigestJob</span>
  <span class="k">schedule</span>: <span class="v">every day at 8am</span>
<span class="k">nightly_backup</span>:
  <span class="k">class</span>: <span class="v">NightlyBackupJob</span>
  <span class="k">schedule</span>: <span class="v">every day at 2am</span></pre>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="figcap">
        <svg class="arrow" viewBox="0 0 40 34" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M34 3 C 20 2, 6 10, 8 26 M8 26 L2 18 M8 26 L16 22"/></svg>
        <span>The schedule you already keep <em>is</em> the config. Stablemate reads it on boot and watches every line.</span>
