    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== HOW IT WORKS ===== %>
<section class="section" id="how">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-intro">
      <p class="kicker">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="flow h2">It's genuinely this simple.</h2>
      <p class="sub">Two minutes, tops. Then Stablemate stays out of your way — and only ever speaks up when <em>something's actually wrong</em>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__no">Step one</div>
        <h3>Add the gem</h3>
        <p>One line in your Gemfile. Bundle. That's the whole install.</p>
        <code class="chip"><span class="k">gem</span> <span class="v">"stablemate"</span></code>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__no">Step two</div>
        <h3>Paste your key</h3>
        <p>On boot, every recurring job signs itself up. <em>You don't lift a finger.</em></p>
        <code class="chip"><span class="k">STABLEMATE_KEY</span>=<span class="v">sk_live_…</span></code>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step__no">Step three</div>
        <h3>Get on with your day</h3>
        <p>Each run checks in. Miss the window and an email lands. <em>No news is good news.</em></p>
        <div class="pings">
          <div class="ping ping--up"><span class="dot"></span> daily_digest · checked in 08:00</div>
          <div class="ping ping--down"><span class="dot"></span> nightly_backup · down · we emailed you</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== recurring.yml ===== %>
<section class="soft" id="spec">
  <div class="wrap two">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">Native to Solid Queue</p>
      <h2 class="flow h2">Your <span class="mark">recurring.yml</span> is already the to-do list.</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><span class="tick">✓</span><div>Reads <b>config/recurring.yml</b> on boot — not one line changes in your job code.</div></li>
        <li><span class="tick">✓</span><div>A grace window per job, so a slow night never cries wolf.</div></li>
        <li><span class="tick">✓</span><div>Keys you can rotate — shown once, hashed at rest, useless the moment they leak.</div></li>
        <li><span class="tick">✓</span><div>Delete the job, delete the monitor. Your schedule stays the single source of truth.</div></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <figure class="figure">
      <div class="specimen" style="background:var(--paper)">
        <div class="specimen__bar">Watching now <span class="fn">4 monitors · all in sync</span></div>
        <div style="padding:6px 0">
          <div class="ledgerrow"><span>stripe_reconcile</span><span style="color:var(--sage)">● healthy · 3:00am</span></div>
          <div class="ledgerrow"><span>daily_digest</span><span style="color:var(--sage)">● healthy · 8:00am</span></div>
          <div class="ledgerrow" style="color:var(--rails-deep)"><span>nightly_backup</span><span>● down · 4h ago</span></div>
          <div class="ledgerrow"><span>clear_sessions</span><span style="color:var(--ink-faint)">○ waiting for first ping</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ===== THE EMAIL ===== %>
<section class="section" id="mail">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-intro">
      <p class="kicker">The email</p>
      <h2 class="flow h2">When we do email you, it's worth reading.</h2>
      <p class="sub">The email you'd get the moment a job misses — and the <%= ping_retention_days %>-day trail it links to.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mail-grid">
      <div class="notice">
        <div class="notice__hd">▲ A job went quiet <span class="stamp2">03 Jul · 06:04</span></div>
        <div class="notice__bd">
          <span class="lbl">to:</span> you@yourapp.com<br>
          <span class="lbl">subject:</span> <span class="em">nightly_backup hasn't checked in</span>
          <hr>
          We expected a ping by <b>02:15</b>.<br>
          Last one landed <b>26 hours ago</b> (02 Jul, 02:09).<br><br>
          → View monitor · Pause alerts · Rotate key
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="ledger">
          <div class="ledger__head"><b>nightly_backup</b> · last <%= ping_retention_days %> days</div>
          <%#
            Server-rendered demo ledger (no client JS): a deterministic, ~2-incident
            pattern over ping_retention_days. Two "down" days form the incidents, a
            few "warn" days around them; the rest are healthy at a gently varying
            height. Indices are clamped to the retention window so the pattern holds
            for any retention value.
          %>
          <% days = ping_retention_days %>
          <% down_days = [12, 13, 58].select { |i| i < days } %>
          <% warn_days = [11, 57, 72].select { |i| i < days } %>
          <div class="bars" aria-hidden="true">
            <% days.times do |i| %>
              <% if down_days.include?(i) %>
                <div class="bar down" style="height:24px"></div>
              <% elsif warn_days.include?(i) %>
                <div class="bar warn" style="height:34px"></div>
              <% else %>
                <div class="bar" style="height:<%= 30 + ((i * 7) % 14) %>px"></div>
              <% end %>
            <% end %>
          </div>
          <div class="ledger__foot">
            <span><span class="up">■</span> healthy 97.8%</span>
            <span><span class="dn">■</span> 2 incidents</span>
            <span>back up in ~34m avg</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="big-num tnum">97.8<span class="pct">%</span></div>
          <p class="marginnote">A paper trail for every job — kept whether or not anyone's watching.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

